servinfosub.title: DTC Detecting Condition and Trouble Area

ptxt.emph: P0532: A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor “A” Circuit Low

entry.ptxt: Output voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit is lower than 0.15 V for 5 sec.
(1 D/C detection logic but MIL does not light up)

item.ptxt: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor and/or its circuit

ptxt.emph: P0533: A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor “A” Circuit High

entry.ptxt: Output voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit is higher than 4.93 V for 5 sec.
(1 D/C detection logic but MIL does not light up)
A/C refrigerant pressure sensor ground circuit
A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit
A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit

s1.ptxt: Start engine and operate A/C for 10 sec.

testgroup.question: Was “Engine and Emission Control System Check” performed?

action.ptxt: Go to Engine and Emission Control System Check:J24B .

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit check

test1.ptxt: Turn OFF ignition switch and disconnect connector from A/C refrigerant pressure sensor.
Check for proper terminal connection to A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.
If connections are OK, turn ignition switch to ON position.
Check that voltage between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit (A1) and ground circuit (A3) is 5 V.

testgroup.question: Is it in good condition?

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit check

test1.ptxt: Check that voltage between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit (A1) and vehicle body ground is 5 V.

testgroup.question: Is it in good condition?

paragroup.ptxt: Repair or replace defective wire harness.
If this DTC is detected again, substitute a known-good ECM and recheck.

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit check

test1.ptxt: Turn OFF ignition switch and disconnect connectors from ECM.
Check for proper terminal connection to ECM connectors.
If connections are OK, check that A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit (A1) is as follows.

item.ptxt: Wiring harness resistance of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit is less than 3 Ω.
Insulation resistance of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit is infinity between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor and vehicle body ground.
Insulation resistance of wire harness is infinity between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit terminal and each terminal at A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.
Circuit voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor power supply circuit is 0 – 1 V with ignition switch in ON position.

testgroup.question: Is it in good condition?

action.ptxt: Substitute a known-good ECM and recheck.
Repair or replace defective wire harness.

testgroup.title: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit check

test1.ptxt: Turn OFF ignition switch and disconnect connectors from ECM.
Check for proper terminal connection to ECM connectors.
If connections are OK, check that A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit (A2) is as follows.

item.ptxt: Wiring harness resistance of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit is less than 3 Ω.
Insulation resistance of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit is infinity between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor and vehicle body ground.
Insulation resistance of wire harness is infinity between A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit terminal and each terminal at A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.
Circuit voltage of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor signal circuit is 0 – 1 V with ignition switch in ON position.

testgroup.question: Is it in good condition?

action.ptxt: Repair or replace defective wire harness.

test1.ptxt: Check A/C refrigerant pressure sensor. A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor and Its Circuit Inspection:J24B and N32A Model

action.ptxt: Substitute a known-good ECM and recheck.
